# Alert

An inline callout that surfaces an important message.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/alert
import ui/icon

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  alert.root([alert.info(), attribute.class("w-full max-w-lg")], [
    alert.icon([], [icon.info([])]),
    alert.title([], [html.text("New version available")]),
    alert.description([], [
      html.text("Update now to pick up the latest elements and fixes."),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

## Installation

Install this element and its dependencies with the Drip CLI:

```sh
gleam run -m drip -- add alert
```

## Usage

```gleam
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/alert
import ui/icon

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  alert.root([alert.info()], [
    alert.icon([], [icon.info([])]),
    alert.title([], [html.text("Heads up")]),
    alert.description([], [html.text("Something to note.")]),
    alert.close([], [icon.x([])]),
  ])
}
```

## Variants

Six semantic variants, each pairing an accent color with an icon slot to convey intent at a glance.

### Info

Informative. The lowest-urgency signal in the set.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/alert
import ui/icon

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  alert.root([alert.info(), attribute.class("w-full max-w-lg")], [
    alert.icon([], [icon.info([])]),
    alert.title([], [html.text("Heads up")]),
    alert.description([], [
      html.text("This action is reversible for the next 24 hours."),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Success

Affirmative. Signals that something completed.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/alert
import ui/icon

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  alert.root([alert.success(), attribute.class("w-full max-w-lg")], [
    alert.icon([], [icon.circle_check([])]),
    alert.title([], [html.text("Webhook verified")]),
    alert.description([], [
      html.text("We received a 200 from your endpoint within 80ms."),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Warning

Cautionary. Heightened priority, one step short of failure.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/alert
import ui/icon

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  alert.root([alert.warning(), attribute.class("w-full max-w-lg")], [
    alert.icon([], [icon.triangle_alert([])]),
    alert.title([], [html.text("Approaching rate limit")]),
    alert.description([], [
      html.text("You've used 87% of this hour's request budget."),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Error

Failure. The highest-urgency signal in the set.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/alert
import ui/icon

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  alert.root([alert.error(), attribute.class("w-full max-w-lg")], [
    alert.icon([], [icon.circle_x([])]),
    alert.title([], [html.text("Deployment failed")]),
    alert.description([], [
      html.text("Build #2413 exited with status 1. Check the logs for details."),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Accent

Promotional. The brand-forward variant.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/alert
import ui/icon

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  alert.root([alert.accent(), attribute.class("w-full max-w-lg")], [
    alert.icon([], [icon.sparkles([])]),
    alert.title([], [html.text("Theme it your way")]),
    alert.description([], [
      html.text(
        "Every element ships with CSS variables. Swap palettes, radius, and
        motion without touching markup. ",
      ),
      html.a([attribute.href("#"), attribute.class("text-accent")], [
        html.text("Learn more"),
      ]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Neutral

Subdued. Carries a message without coloring its intent.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/alert
import ui/icon

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  alert.root([alert.neutral(), attribute.class("w-full max-w-lg")], [
    alert.icon([], [icon.book_open_text([])]),
    alert.title([], [html.text("Tip")]),
    alert.description([], [
      html.text(
        "Prefer composing variants over building one-off alerts;
        every slot here is part of the public API.",
      ),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

## Examples

Extend an alert with inline actions, a close button, or a full-width banner.

### Actions

Anchor inline buttons under the description with the actions slot.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/alert
import ui/button
import ui/icon

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  alert.root([alert.error(), attribute.class("w-full max-w-lg")], [
    alert.icon([], [icon.circle_x([])]),
    alert.title([], [html.text("Deployment failed")]),
    alert.description([], [
      html.text("Build #2413 exited with status 1. Check the logs for details."),
    ]),
    alert.actions([], [
      button.button([button.primary(), button.sm()], [
        html.text("View logs"),
      ]),
      button.button([button.destructive(), button.sm()], [
        html.text("Rollback"),
      ]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Dismissible

Add a close button via the close slot.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/alert
import ui/icon

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  alert.root([alert.info(), attribute.class("w-full max-w-lg")], [
    alert.icon([], [icon.info([])]),
    alert.title([], [html.text("Preview mode")]),
    alert.description([], [
      html.text("Changes stay local until you publish this draft."),
    ]),
    alert.close([], [icon.x([])]),
  ])
}
```

### Banner

Use the banner attribute for app-level system messages.

```gleam
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/alert
import ui/icon

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  alert.root([alert.warning(), alert.banner()], [
    alert.icon([], [icon.triangle_alert([])]),
    alert.title([], [html.text("Scheduled maintenance window")]),
    alert.description([], [
      html.text(
        "eu-west-1 will be offline 02:00–02:30 UTC on
        May 2 for planned database migration.",
      ),
    ]),
    alert.close([], [icon.x([])]),
  ])
}
```

## API Reference

### Variants

Six variant attributes, one per semantic intent. Pass one into the root's attribute list.

| Variant | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `alert.info()` | Informational note for non-urgent messages. |
| `alert.success()` | Positive confirmation for a completed action. |
| `alert.warning()` | Caution required, not yet failing. |
| `alert.error()` | A failure that requires user attention. |
| `alert.accent()` | Brand-aligned promotional alert for feature announcements. |
| `alert.neutral()` | The default quiet surface for in-doc callouts and tips. |

### Elements

The root container and the composable child elements that fill its regions.

| Element | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `alert.root(attrs, children)` | The root container. Holds the slots and carries the variant attribute. |
| `alert.icon(attrs, children)` | Leading icon tile. Inherits color and background from variant. |
| `alert.title(attrs, children)` | Short, bold heading for the alert. |
| `alert.description(attrs, children)` | Supporting text under the title. |
| `alert.actions(attrs, children)` | Trailing element under the description for inline action buttons. |
| `alert.close(attrs, children)` | Trailing close button for dismissible alerts. |

### Attributes

Pass these into the root's attribute list.

| Attribute | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `alert.banner()` | Squares the corners and keeps only the bottom border so the alert spans its container edge-to-edge. |
| `attribute.role("status")` | Announces info and success alerts politely when they're inserted dynamically. |
| `attribute.role("alert")` | Announces warning and error alerts assertively, interrupting the current utterance. |

### Selectors

CSS selectors stamped on the alert's markup, available for overriding or layering app-specific styles.

| Selector | Matches |
| --- | --- |
| `[data-slot="alert"]` | The root container. |
| `[data-variant="info\|success\|..."]` | The root, tagged with its active semantic variant. |
| `[data-style="banner"]` | The root, tagged when the banner attribute is applied. |
| `[data-slot="alert-icon"]` | Leading icon tile. |
| `[data-slot="alert-title"]` | Heading inside the alert. |
| `[data-slot="alert-description"]` | Supporting text inside the alert. |
| `[data-slot="alert-actions"]` | Trailing row of inline action buttons. |
| `[data-slot="alert-close"]` | Trailing close button. |

## Accessibility

**Opt-in live-region roles.** Alerts ship without a live-region role, so announcements are up to you. Add role="alert" to errors and warnings to interrupt the screen reader as soon as the alert appears, or role="status" to info and success to announce politely after the current utterance. Leave neutral and accent role-free unless they carry something worth announcing.

